<p>There's no <code>detail</code> property yet. But no worries, creating that is easy! It all happens
inside of our <code>ApiExceptionSubscriber</code>. </p>
<h2 id="adding-exception-message-as-detail">Adding Exception Message as detail <a class="headerlink" href="helpful-details-key#adding-exception-message-as-detail" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Very simply, we say <code>$apiProblem-&gt;set()</code> since that allows us to put in new fields.
And we'll pass that <code>detail</code> and <code>$e-&gt;getMessage()</code>:</p>
